<DOC><DOCNO> AP880713-0093 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-13-88 1155EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Britain-Helicopter 1stLd-Writethru   07-13 0174</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Britain-Helicopter, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0622,0177</SECOND><HEAD>Helicopter with 21 Aboard Ditches in North Sea</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Leads with 2 grafs with all reported safe. Picks up 2nd pvs,`The coast...</NOTE><DATELINE>ABERDEEN, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A helicopter with 21 people aboardditched into the North Sea today, and two helicopters and alifeboat rescued all the occupants, the coast guard said.   There were no immediate reports of injuries.   The coast guard in Aberdeen said the Sikorsky helicopter made acontrolled landing onto the ocean surface 17 miles east of Lerwickin the Shetland Islands.   Most helicopter traffic in the area serves the oil rigs of theNorth Sea, but it was not immediately known whether this one wasferrying oil workers.   Press Association, the domestic news agency, said the helicopterlanded upright and stayed afloat with the occupants remaininginside, but it said weather conditions were rough.   The coast guard said it sent a helicopter from Sumburgh in theShetlands to mount a rescue operation, along with a Shell Oil Co.helicopter and a lifeboat from Lerwick.</TEXT></DOC>